      Auxiliary method for valid. Determines if a subtree based on node is a valid subtree.
      Parameters:
      node - The root of the subtree to test for validity.
      minNode - The node of the minimum data in the current subtree.
      maxNode - The node of the maximum data in the current subtree.
      Returns:
      true if the subtree base on node is valid, false otherwise.

    • inOrder

      public ArrayList<CountedItem<T>> inOrder()
      Returns a list of the data in the current tree. The list contents are in order from smallest to largest. Not thread safe as it assumes contents of the tree are not changed by an external thread during the loop.
      Returns:
      The contents of this tree as a list of data.

    • isValid

      public boolean isValid()
      Determines if this tree is a valid BST; i.e. a node's left child data is smaller than its data, and its right child data is greater than its data, and a node's height is equal to the maximum of the heights of its two children (empty child nodes have a height of 0), plus 1.
      Returns:
      true if this tree is a valid BST, false otherwise.

    • levelOrder

      public ArrayList<CountedItem<T>> levelOrder()
      Returns a list of the data in the current tree. The list contents are in node level order starting from the root node. Helps determine the structure of the tree. Not thread safe as it assumes contents of the tree are not changed by an external thread during the loop.
      Returns:
      this tree data as a list of data.

    • preOrder

      public ArrayList<CountedItem<T>> preOrder()
      Returns a list of the data in the current tree. The list contents are in node preorder. Not thread safe as it assumes contents of the tree are not changed by an external thread during the loop.
      Returns:
      The contents of this tree as a list of data.

    • remove

      public void remove(CountedItem<T> countedItem)
      Removes data from the tree. Decrements the node count, and if the count is 0, removes the node entirely.
      Parameters:
      countedItem - Data to decrement or remove.

    • resetComparisons

      public void resetComparisons()
      Resets the comparison count to 0.

    • retrieve

      public CountedItem<T> retrieve(CountedItem<T> key)
      Retrieves a copy of data matching key (key should have data count of 0). Returning a complete CountedItem gives access to the data and its count.
      Parameters:
      key - The key to look for.
      Returns:
      The complete CountedItem that matches key, null otherwise.
